Master's thesis consists of independently conducted research, formatting and defence of the thesis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop knowledge and skills for writing a research paper.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has defended the Master's thesis: - recognizes the problems and/or issues which occur in the research area, is able to state a research problem and justify the choice of topic; - is able to formulate the research objective and questions/tasks according to the research problem; - is able to handle theoretical and methodical knowledge; - is able to determine the researched subjects/material and select a research method; - is able to collect and analyse data according to the chosen methodology and describe the research process; - is able to present the research results according to the research aim, questions, and tasks; - is able to interpret and discuss the research results; - is able to draw conclusions; - is able to express ideas, following the rules of the Estonian language and requirements for scientific language; - is able to structure and format research as required; - is able to present and defend the research orally.
